The mother of a senator representing Kogi Central Senatorial District Ahmed Ogembe Salawu and Chairman of Somolu Local Government, Abdul Hamed Salawu, Alhaja Wulemotu Salawu, is dead. Alhaja Salawu, who owns Equalrights Food Mart, died in Lagos on Monday. She hailed from Ilesa in Osun State,   Independent Newspapers loses board chairman     Forum backs Tinubu’s aspiration     Fed Govt planning N15b revitalisation funds for poly,…   She was 72. She was a popular food vender for over five decades and known for her Amala delicacies of Equalrights Food Mart in Somolu, Alausa and Berger bus stop. A statement by Owolabi Oseni, the Chief Press Secretary to the Somolu Local Government Chairman, the late businesswoman died after taking breakfast.